9:
That was an excellent performance,
Lyra! Great job as always.
14:
I didn't expect such a big audience.
I'm really grateful so many people
could hear my music.
17:
It looks like word of mouth about
you is spreading outside of Palpebra!
20:
I wouldn't be surprised if you get
invitations to play in the courts of
foreign kingdoms at this point!
29:
A letter of invitation has arrived for
Lyra—it's from the royal court
orchestra of the Farlands!
39:
I recognize the seal—it's definitely
not fake.
42:
The Farlands... That's one of the
biggest kingdoms in this world, isn't
it?
45:
Indeed. I failed to mention this
before, but I'm actually from there.
51:
Really? Well isn't that just swell! Now
that you've become famous abroad,
you're sure to have one heck of a
warm welcome when you return!
54:
Perhaps...
Though I wonder just how warm a
welcome it will be...
60:
Did something happen to you while
you were there?
62:
The truth is... My parents were
expelled from the royal court. That's
why they came to Palpebra.
65:
So they kicked you out of the
orchestra, waited until you got
famous again, and then re-invited
you?
67:
Not quite... I was only in the Farlands
for a short while—and while I was
very young. I'm sure they don't
realize who I am.
71:
Well, with a history like that, it'd be
understandable if you didn't want to
go.
72:
They caused you a whole lot of
trouble, after all. You must be pretty
conflicted about all this.
74:
Yes. To be honest, I really have no
wish to find out whatever my
parents did to be kicked out... I'd
rather the past stayed in the past.
80:
Is it possible that it wasn't entirely
their fault?
85:
Well, they DID just up and disappear,
leaving Lyra with a mountain of debt.
93:
That melody... I have no doubt I first
heard it when I lived in the Farlands.
98:
Oh, the one you've been practicing
all this time?
101:
Yes. If I travel there, perhaps I can
find out who exactly it was that first
played that melody for me...
103:
I will be accepting the court's
invitation.
108:
At long last, the up-and-coming
violinist we've heard so much about!
Welcome, Lyra!
110:
I am grateful to have been invited to
the royal court of the Farlands. It is
an honor.
113:
I had heard you were working as an
adventurer, but your thoroughly
refined demeanor suggests
otherwise! Are you perhaps of noble
birth?
117:
I'm afraid not—I am merely a
humble adventurer. Now, with
regards to the concert...
120:
This is the hall where you'll be
performing. It's to be a family event,
so you needn't be overly nervous—
122:
Are you all right, my dear? Your
complexion has turned something
dreadful.
126:
Ah, no, I am fine. Apologies.
I was just taken aback—this room
looked familiar.
128:
...There's no doubt about it. This is
the room where I heard the melody...
131:
Miss Lyra, are your preparations all
in order?
134: Yes. I can begin any time.
137:
Ladies and gentlemen, I trust you
are enjoying yourselves?
139:
Our banquet celebrations are far
from over—in fact, we've brought
over a very special guest!
140:
I present to you Lyra Ebelsorte: the
latest musical sensation out of
Palpebra!
143:
Given her remarkable skills, we can
surely expect an excellent, fantastic
performance!
Whenever you are ready, my lady!
149:
Mom, dad... One day, will I be able to
play as beautifully as you?
155:
That's right... That melody...
It was mother and father who
taught me it first.
156:
For all their faults, they managed to
leave me with something valuable
after all.
158:
Perhaps I should be grateful for this
much.
163:
Bravo! Bravissimo!
What a splendid performance!
164:
Lady Lyra, I would be remiss if I did
not ask you: would you be willing to
formally join our court orchestra?
167:
I am beyond grateful for your
invitation, concertmaster. However,
I'm afraid I must decline.
170:
There is somewhere I must go. Or
rather, return. At long last, I think I've
finally realized what my dream in life
is.
175:
As I expected, playing music is very
difficult. Almost as difficult as
cooking.
179:
Haha, don't you worry. There's no
need to rush—you'll get the hang of
it sooner or later. These things take
time.
184:
I must say, I was quite surprised to
hear Lyra say she wanted to be a
music teacher.
188:
Me too. Ever since she came back
from her trip to the Farlands, she's
been so much more... energetic and
lively!
196:
My whole life, I've been so blessed
by those around me, being taught
things, receiving their aid...
200:
Now it's my turn to give something
back in return.
206: Well, when you put it that way!
210:
Okay, Stella, you want to lose the
tension from your arm, but you still
need to get a firm grip on the bow.
Then, move it quickly, with a quick
whoosh!
220:
Don't worry, Stella. This is hardly
something you can pick up in a
single afternoon!
221:
Just like Lyra said—take your time
and don't rush. It will come to you
eventually!
227:
That was it, right there! Great job,
Stella!
236:
I thought that was supposed to take
a long time?! Is Stella a prodigy or
something?
239:
Please teach me more, Lyra. What
should I do next?
245:
Leave it to me! Okay, so next you'll
want to—
